posts.cooked:
Does anyone know if it is possible to do NetworkTables in dart? I could not find any packages for it on pub.dev, and I am not sure it is even possible. Trying to make a flutter desktop app that communicates with our robot. If anyone knows how to do NetworkTables in dart or have ideas on it, please share.

Thanks!

posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked: I don’t know of any implementations, but since the NT4 protocol is built on top of WebSockets, JSON, and MessagePack, it should be doable.
Oh that is nice, will try it out. I assume this is how others have been able to use NetworkTables in python and even rust?
Oh wow, Is this a JS client of NetworkTables?
